[Prior to September 2015, Nepal was divided into 5 regions, which were subdivided into 14 administrative zones and then 75 districts. Chitwan is a district in the Narayani Zone of the Central Region of Nepal and Tanahu is a district in the Gandaki Zone of the Western Region. Maps of Nepal can be seen at http://ncthakur.itgo.com/map04.htm (regions, zones, and districts) and at http://www.healthmap.org/promed/p/139. Nepal is currently divided into 7 federal provinces, which are formed by grouping together the existing districts (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nepalese_Federal_States).

For discussions of scrub typhus, see moderator comments in prior ProMED-mail posts below. - Mod.ML]
